                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1" defective="false">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; four group of lines in the incipit page of the text, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each section of the text, alternating with black lines; names of Hebrew letters in Ps. 118 (e.g., fols. 23vb, 25ra); elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; some other words, e.g., halle luya (e.g., fols. 3vb, 4ra), wä-kaʿǝbä (e.g., fols. 7ra, 20ra), ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 7ra, 74ra), ʾǝgäle (e.g., 20ra, 24vb), wä-tәbl (e.g., fols. 25rb, 26va), wä-ʾәmzә (e.g., fols. 25rb, 26ra).</rubric>
                     <incipit defective="false">
